# Force LF in the working tree on every platform.
#
# LicenseAudit ships committed sample artefacts (out/ reports + audited-
# project SBOMs and the sbom/ capability family). The compiler emits the
# SBOMs with LF on every OS, and the reports are produced with LF too, so
# the only way a regenerated tree could differ from what ships here is a
# checkout that rewrote committed LF to CRLF (core.autocrlf). Every tracked
# file is text (.capa, .json, .txt, .csv, .md, .toml, .sh, LICENSE,
# SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH); a blanket eol=lf is safe and keeps the reproducibility
# diff empty.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Reproducibility inputs, pinned LF for defence in depth.
sbom/SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH text eol=lf
generate.sh            text eol=lf
